reviews.text:
Pretty decent Yats. Food was on par for the place

Their hot sauce wall wasn't as big as the old Valparaiso one (RIP) but they had some goof options
I'm actually a little bummed they didn't have shrimp and grits.  Isn't that a top Cajun dish? Or is that just a thing in New Orleans?  All they had were...

Cajun food in the midwest that's actually good for a change.

Cheap etoufees and gumbos, served up quickly at reasonable prices. Order at the counter. No...
